    tool_output=ToolOutput(
        output='Based on the provided prospectus excerpts, here are the relevant disclosures and rationale for your queries:\n\n### 1. Rationale for Not Reporting Standalone AI Customer Counts\nThe prospectus discloses that the company presents combined metrics for its integrated AI platforms (Grok and X) rather than separate standalone AI counts. The defined metric **"MAU"** explicitly combines users across both platforms, with a methodology to de-duplicate users who access both. The company states it focuses on business fundamentals over standalone user counts:\n\n> *“While MAUs provide an estimated measure of the size and engagement of our user base, we are focused on revenue and operating margin, and manage our business with the objective of driving sustainable revenue growth and profitability rather than with the primary objective of growing or maintaining MAU levels.”* (From [SECTION: PREAMBLE])\n\nThe **definition of MAU** confirms the integrated reporting approach:\n> *“‘MAU’ (or monthly active users) refers to the total number of users who have interacted with Grok or X through web browsers or mobile applications at least once during the 30-day period ending on the date of measurement (“active users”). In presenting combined MAUs across the two platforms, we seek to identify and account for users who access both Grok and X based on sign-in traffic so that such users are not double-counted when measuring MAU.”* (From [SECTION: PREAMBLE])\n\n### 2. Rationale for Reporting Grok Feature MAU Penetration Instead of Distinct AI Subscriber Counts\nThe company reports the number of MAUs *using Grok’s AI features* (117 million as of March 31, 2026) as a key metric to illustrate penetration and engagement within the existing user base of X. This aligns with the strategy to monetize through integration and shows the scale of AI feature adoption across the platform.\n\nKey disclosures on this approach include:\n\n*   **Penetration as a Growth Metric:** *"Of our MAUs, we had approximately 117 million MAUs that used Grok’s AI features as of March 31, 2026. While our subscriber growth has been strong, we believe we are still early in increasing paid penetration across our Grok user base."* (From [SECTION: PREAMBLE])\n*   **Strategic Monetization Path:** The prospectus notes that beyond direct subscription, there may be an incremental monetization opportunity by introducing advertising into the stand-alone Grok offering, indicating a broader monetization strategy beyond counting distinct subscribers. (From [SECTION: PREAMBLE])\n\n### 3. Strategic Advantages & Design Philosophy: Embedded AI Distribution via X vs. Standalone\nThe prospectus extensively details the strategic advantage of embedding Grok within the X platform rather than operating it as a purely standalone service. The core philosophy is **deep integration and vertical synergies**.\n\n**Key Advantages Disclosed:**\n\n1.  **Real-Time Data & Truth-Seeking:** *"A key competitive differentiator is Grok’s deep integration with X, enabling proprietary access to a real-time information stream of approximately 350 million daily posts, which enhances freshness, relevance, and contextual awareness for Grok. This direct, real-time access to the information and human discourse on X enhances Grok’s truth-seeking capabilities..."* (From [SECTION: PREAMBLE])\n2.  **User Engagement & Monetization:** *"X’s scale, real-time engagement, and integration with Grok provide a differentiated foundation for building a unified user experience across communication, content discovery, commerce, and financial services... For enterprises that advertise on X, we offer large-scale user engagement, real-time content, and advanced AI-driven performance marketing tools."* (From [SECTION: PREAMBLE])\n3.  **"Everything App" Vision:** The strategy is to evolve X into an "Everything App" integrating information, communications, payments, and more, with Grok as a core component to enhance discovery, analysis, and personalization, thereby increasing utility and reducing friction for paid features. (From [SECTION: PREAMBLE])\n4.  **Vertical Integration & Control:** The company believes its control over the full stack—from compute infrastructure (COLOSSUS) to the AI model (Grok) and the distribution/data platform (X)—is a unique structural advantage in the AI industry. (From [SECTION: PREAMBLE])\n\n### 4. Risk Factors Related to the Integrated Business Model\nThe integrated model introduces specific risks that are disclosed:\n\n*   **Dependency on X Platform Health:** *"A decline in users on the X platform, or the volume or quality of their content on the X platform, could also impact the ongoing development of our AI product, which in part utilizes data and user-generated content from the X platform."* (From [SECTION: PREAMBLE])\n*   **Operational and Competitive Risks:** The company faces risks from a *"highly dynamic and rapidly evolving"* AI market, including *"intense competition for user attention"* that can cause usage metrics for applications like Grok to *"fluctuate significantly."* Executing the integrated strategy involves risks of *"near-term operational disruptions, integration inefficiencies... and uneven customer adoption."* (From [SECTION: PREAMBLE])\n*   **Regulatory and Misuse Risks:** The integrated platforms are subject to complex global regulations regarding AI, privacy, and content. The prospectus highlights specific risks related to *"misuse of our AI systems"* and investigations concerning allegations that AI products were used to create harmful content. (From [SECTION: PREAMBLE])\n\n**In summary,** the prospectus presents the integrated model as a strategic choice to leverage X\'s massive, real-time user base and data for Grok\'s competitive advantage in AI, while managing and reporting the business based on combined platform engagement and revenue profitability rather than standalone AI metrics.',
